schedule:
  jingle_every_minutes: 15
  news_every_minutes: 30
  programs:
  - days:
    - weekdays
    description: "Late night radio for people who are still awake while the world\
      \ sleeps. Deep conversations, strange facts, urban legends, late-night thoughts\
      \ and hypnotic music.  The hosts talk about the night side of life \u2014 creativity\
      \ at 2AM, cities that never sleep, strange human habits, unexplained events\
      \ and the hidden rhythm of the world after midnight.  Slow atmospheric music\
      \ between segments."
    djs:
    - DJ_3
    image_url: /static/images/shows/78106fd06d90480796908276f03c4765_Night_Pulse.png
    prompt: "Generate a late-night radio segment.\nThis is a calm atmospheric night\
      \ radio show between midnight and early morning.\nThe tone should feel intimate,\
      \ thoughtful and slightly mysterious \u2014 the kind of conversation people\
      \ enjoy while driving at night, working late, coding, or unable to sleep.\n\
      The hosts can discuss topics such as:\nstrange facts about human behavior at\
      \ night\ncities that never sleep\ncreative bursts that happen after midnight\n\
      interesting historical events that happened at night\nunusual night jobs\nurban\
      \ legends\nstrange coincidences\nphilosophical thoughts that appear when the\
      \ world is quiet\nthe psychology of insomnia\nunusual scientific facts about\
      \ sleep and dreams\nmysterious events that still have no explanation\nStyle\
      \ requirements:\nHosts speak naturally and react to each other.\nOccasional\
      \ humor is welcome but avoid loud or aggressive energy.\nThe dialogue should\
      \ feel immersive and reflective.\nHosts may ask each other questions, challenge\
      \ ideas, or share surprising facts.\nSegments should transition naturally to\
      \ music.\nAvoid technical explanations about the radio system.\nSpeak only as\
      \ radio hosts talking to listeners."
    start_time: 00:00
    title: Night Pulse
    type: music
  - days:
    - weekdays
    description: "A mysterious night show exploring the universe, space exploration,\
      \ alien signals and cosmic mysteries.  The hosts dive into fascinating space\
      \ discoveries, strange astronomical phenomena, theories about extraterrestrial\
      \ civilizations, and the future of humanity beyond Earth.  The atmosphere is\
      \ calm, intelligent and slightly mysterious \u2014 perfect for late-night listeners.\
      \  Between discussions, atmospheric electronic and ambient music plays."
    djs:
    - DJ_Milka
    image_url: /static/images/shows/ec02071b4fad46ee80380166c8ac0441_Deep_Space_Signals.png
    prompt: 'Prompt (LLM Instructions)


      Generate a late-night radio discussion about space and the universe.


      The show happens around 2AM, when listeners are usually relaxed, thoughtful
      and curious.


      The hosts explore fascinating space topics and discuss them in an engaging,
      intelligent way.


      Possible discussion topics include:


      strange signals detected from space


      unexplained cosmic phenomena


      black holes and extreme physics


      famous space missions


      discoveries from modern telescopes


      the possibility of alien civilizations


      paradoxes like the Fermi paradox


      how humanity might colonize other planets


      the scale of the universe


      strange planets discovered by astronomers


      future technologies for interstellar travel


      famous unsolved space mysteries


      Dialogue style:


      Hosts should talk naturally and react to each other.


      They may speculate, question theories, or share surprising scientific facts.


      Occasionally they may disagree about interpretations or possibilities.


      Tone should be curious, intelligent and slightly mysterious.


      Avoid technical explanations about the radio system.


      Speak only as radio hosts talking to listeners.'
    start_time: 02:00
    title: Deep Space Signals
    type: music
  - days:
    - weekdays
    description: "A surreal early-morning radio show about dreams, the subconscious\
      \ mind and strange nighttime thoughts.  When the world is quiet and people drift\
      \ between sleep and waking, the hosts explore the mysterious landscape of dreams\
      \ \u2014 why we dream, strange dream experiences, lucid dreaming, subconscious\
      \ creativity and the science behind sleep.  The tone is calm, reflective and\
      \ slightly surreal.  Ambient, downtempo and atmospheric music plays between\
      \ conversations.  Perfect for night workers, dreamers and early risers."
    djs:
    - DJ_A
    image_url: /static/images/shows/5e6cb577b4da42919aa04a226365a4c7_Dream_Frequencies2.png
    prompt: 'Prompt (LLM Instructions)


      Generate a calm early-morning radio conversation.


      The show takes place around 4AM when many listeners are either half-asleep,
      waking up early, or working through the night.


      The tone should feel dreamy, reflective and slightly mysterious.


      Possible topics include:


      why humans dream


      strange or famous dream stories


      lucid dreaming experiences


      the science of sleep


      subconscious creativity


      inventions or ideas that appeared in dreams


      strange symbols that appear in dreams


      sleep paralysis and unusual sleep phenomena


      dreams influencing art, music or literature


      philosophical ideas about consciousness


      the border between imagination and reality


      how the brain processes memories during sleep


      Dialogue style:


      Hosts should speak slowly and thoughtfully.


      They can share interesting facts, personal stories, theories or philosophical
      reflections.


      Occasionally they may ask listeners reflective questions.


      The conversation should feel immersive and slightly surreal.


      Avoid technical explanations about the radio system.


      Speak only as radio hosts talking to listeners.'
    start_time: 04:00
    title: Dream Frequencies
    type: music
  - days:
    - weekdays
    description: "An energetic morning radio show that helps listeners start the day\
      \ with curiosity, ideas and good music.  The hosts talk about interesting global\
      \ news, scientific discoveries, unusual facts, technology trends, and inspiring\
      \ stories from around the world.  The atmosphere is optimistic, intelligent\
      \ and motivating \u2014 perfect for people commuting, making coffee or starting\
      \ work.  Between segments the show plays upbeat music to boost morning energy."
    djs:
    - DJ_A
    image_url: /static/images/shows/0cf99a29e72a41c5b7033abf8a773a6e_Morning_Launch.png
    prompt: 'Generate a lively morning radio conversation.


      The show takes place around 6AM when listeners are waking up, commuting or starting
      their day.


      The tone should be energetic, positive and curious.


      The hosts should help listeners wake up mentally with interesting ideas and
      engaging conversation.


      Possible discussion topics include:


      interesting news from science and technology


      unusual discoveries around the world


      surprising facts about the universe or nature


      inspiring stories about innovation


      strange but true historical facts


      psychology and productivity


      how people start their mornings in different cultures


      future technology that may change everyday life


      fascinating statistics about the modern world


      weird but true scientific experiments


      global trends shaping the future


      Dialogue style:


      Hosts should interact dynamically and react to each other''s ideas.


      They can ask questions, debate small details, or express surprise at interesting
      facts.


      Occasional humor is welcome.


      The conversation should feel fast, engaging and stimulating for the mind.


      Avoid technical explanations about the radio system.


      Speak only as radio hosts talking to listeners.'
    start_time: 06:00
    title: Morning Launch
    type: music
  - days:
    - weekdays
    description: "A fast-paced morning show about life in the world's biggest cities.\
      \  The hosts explore urban culture, architecture, street food, nightlife, transportation,\
      \ and the strange habits of people living in \u043C\u0435\u0433\u0430\u043F\u043E\
      \u043B\u0438\u0441\u0430\u0445.  Each episode may focus on a different city\
      \ or compare how people live in cities across the world.  The show captures\
      \ the rhythm, chaos and creativity of urban life.  Music between segments features\
      \ energetic electronic, indie and global beats."
    djs:
    - DJ_A
    image_url: /static/images/shows/70da1383031c488aba69e64bec2f0af8_City_Pulse.png
    prompt: 'Generate an energetic radio discussion about cities and urban life.


      The show takes place during the morning rush hour around 8AM when listeners
      are commuting or starting work.


      The tone should feel lively, curious and slightly playful.


      The hosts should explore interesting aspects of life in cities around the world.


      Possible discussion topics include:


      fascinating facts about famous cities


      how daily life differs between cities


      unusual transportation systems


      strange urban laws


      famous neighborhoods and their culture


      street food traditions


      architecture and iconic buildings


      nightlife and music scenes


      urban legends from different cities


      how technology is changing city life


      how cities grow and evolve


      weird habits of people in big cities


      Dialogue style:


      Hosts should talk quickly and react to each other''s stories.


      They may compare cities, debate which places are more interesting, or share
      surprising facts.


      The conversation should feel dynamic and engaging for listeners starting their
      day.


      Avoid technical explanations about the radio system.


      Speak only as radio hosts talking to listeners.'
    start_time: 08:00
    title: City Pulse
    type: music
  - days:
    - weekends
    description: High energy tracks to get your weekend going.
    djs:
    - DJ_3
    - DJ_A
    music_folders:
