    title: Urban Stories
    type: music
  - days:
    - everyday
    description: A show exploring the strange and fascinating mechanics of the human
      mind.  The hosts dive into psychology, cognitive science, human behavior and
      the hidden patterns that influence how people think and make decisions.  Listeners
      discover surprising facts about memory, emotions, perception, biases and the
      weird tricks the brain plays on us every day.  The show is smart, curious and
      sometimes a little mind-bending.  Music between segments features lo-fi, chill
      electronic and experimental sounds.
    djs:
    - DJ_3
    image_url: /static/images/shows/9936e290ac8f4a02a7db326a07f313fb_Human_Mind_Lab.png
    music_folders:
    - E:/My_Music/AI Music SUNO
    prompt: 'Generate an engaging radio discussion about the human mind and psychology.


      The show takes place in the late afternoon around 4PM when listeners are still
      active but starting to feel mentally tired, so the discussion should be stimulating
      and intriguing.


      The hosts explore interesting aspects of human psychology and behavior.


      Possible discussion topics include:


      cognitive biases that influence decisions


      strange tricks the brain plays on perception


      memory illusions


      why people believe conspiracy theories


      the psychology of habits


      how emotions affect decision making


      social behavior and group psychology


      how attention works


      why people procrastinate


      how the brain processes music and art


      the science of motivation


      strange psychological experiments


      Dialogue style:


      Hosts should analyze ideas, react to surprising facts and occasionally challenge
      each other''s interpretations.


      They may use small thought experiments to involve listeners.


      The tone should be curious, intelligent and slightly playful.


      Avoid technical explanations about the radio system.


      Speak only as radio hosts talking to listeners.'
    start_time: '16:00'
    title: Human Mind Lab
    type: music
  - days:
    - everyday
    description: "The high-energy evening show for people heading home after work.\
      \  Fast conversations, surprising facts, music discoveries and entertaining\
      \ debates keep the energy up during the busiest hours of the day.  The hosts\
      \ react to trending topics, unusual stories and curious ideas while introducing\
      \ energetic music perfect for the drive home.  The show is dynamic, fun and\
      \ slightly chaotic \u2014 like city traffic itself."
    djs:
    - DJ_A
    image_url: /static/images/shows/10059640e30b4f67b2abd72aeaa7a5fc_Drive_Time_Energy.png
    prompt: 'Generate an energetic radio show conversation for evening drive time.


      The show takes place around 6PM when listeners are commuting, driving home,
      or finishing work.


      The tone should be energetic, entertaining and fast-paced.


      The hosts should sound lively and occasionally playful with each other.


