    type: music
  - days:
    - everyday
    description: 'Our flagship night show: explores the vast mysteries of space and
      the untapped potential of the human spirit.'
    djs:
    - DJ_A
    - DJ_3
    image_url: https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1451187580459-43490279c0fa?w=800&q=80
    music_folders:
    - E:/My_Music/AI Music SUNO
    prompt: "Topic:\nSpace and Human Potential\n\nFacts for AI prompt:\n\nSpace officially\
      \ begins at the K\xE1rm\xE1n line, about 100 km (62 miles) above Earth.\n\n\
      Commercial airplanes fly at around 10\u201312 km altitude, meaning space is\
      \ only about 30\u201340 times higher than typical flight altitude.\n\nThe International\
      \ Space Station (ISS) orbits Earth at about 400 km (250 miles) above the surface.\n\
      \nThe ISS travels at approximately 28,000 km/h (17,500 mph) and completes one\
      \ orbit around Earth every 90 minutes.\n\nAstronauts aboard the ISS experience\
      \ 16 sunrises and sunsets every day.\n\nSince 1961, fewer than 700 humans have\
      \ traveled to space.\n\nEarth's population exceeds 8 billion people, meaning\
      \ spaceflight remains extremely rare.\n\nThe first human in space was Yuri Gagarin\
      \ on April 12, 1961.\n\nThe first humans landed on the Moon during Apollo 11\
      \ in 1969.\n\nNeil Armstrong became the first person to walk on the Moon.\n\n\
      The Moon is about 384,400 km (238,855 miles) from Earth.\n\nLight from the Sun\
      \ takes about 8 minutes and 20 seconds to reach Earth.\n\nThe nearest star system,\
      \ Alpha Centauri, is about 4.24 light-years away.\n\nOne light-year equals about\
      \ 9.46 trillion kilometers (5.88 trillion miles).\n\nThe Milky Way galaxy contains\
      \ approximately 100\u2013400 billion stars.\n\nScientists estimate there may\
      \ be hundreds of billions of galaxies in the observable universe.\n\nSpace has\
      \ no atmosphere, meaning sound cannot travel.\n\nTemperatures in space can range\
      \ from about +120\xB0C (248\xB0F) in sunlight to \u2013150\xB0C (\u2013238\xB0\
      F) in shade.\n\nIn microgravity, astronauts can grow 3\u20135 cm taller due\
      \ to spinal expansion.\n\nBone density can decrease by 1\u20132% per month during\
      \ long missions in microgravity.\n\nAstronauts on the ISS receive significantly\
      \ higher levels of cosmic radiation than people on Earth.\n\nThe longest single\
      \ spaceflight by a human was 437 days, completed by cosmonaut Valeri Polyakov\
      \ aboard the Mir space station.\n\nTwo spacecraft launched in 1977, Voyager\
      \ 1 and Voyager 2, are now traveling in interstellar space.\n\nVoyager 1 is\
      \ currently over 23 billion kilometers (14 billion miles) away from Earth.\n\
      \nEach Voyager spacecraft carries a Golden Record containing sounds, music,\
      \ greetings in 55 languages, and images of life on Earth.\n\nMars has a day\
      \ length of 24 hours and 39 minutes, similar to Earth's day.\n\nGravity on Mars\
      \ is about 38% of Earth's gravity.\n\nSurface temperatures on Mars can drop\
      \ to about \u2013125\xB0C (\u2013195\xB0F).\n\nThe global space economy is estimated\
      \ to be worth over $500 billion annually.\n\nReusable rocket technology has\
      \ reduced launch costs from roughly $20,000 per kilogram in the 1960s to about\
      \ $2,000 per kilogram today.\n\nHuman missions to the Moon are planned again\
      \ through programs such as Artemis, aiming to establish long-term lunar presence.\n\
      \nSome scientists believe humans may eventually become a multi-planetary species,\
      \ living on both Earth and other worlds such as the Moon or Mars."
    start_time: '22:00'
    title: Space and Human Potential - Night Show
