    prompt: "Generate a long-form, structured podcast dialogue about UFO and extraterrestrial\
      \ theories and facts. The output must be a natural conversation between multiple\
      \ speakers (do not specify or limit the number of participants \u2014 it may\
      \ vary). The discussion should feel authentic, intelligent, and immersive.\n\
      \nLength requirement: the full dialogue should be approximately 30 minutes of\
      \ spoken content.\n\nStructure requirements:\n\nDivide the conversation clearly\
      \ into 5 parts (Part 1\u2013Part 5).\n\nEach part should focus on a distinct\
      \ theme, question, or angle.\n\nMaintain logical flow and progression between\
      \ parts.\n\nConversations must be dynamic and organic, not scripted or robotic.\n\
      \nDialogue style:\n\nLong, meaningful exchanges.\n\nParticipants may interrupt,\
      \ challenge, and disagree respectfully.\n\nThey do not have to agree \u2014\
      \ debate and differing interpretations are encouraged.\n\nThe tone should reflect\
      \ intelligent, analytical speakers who know the material well.\n\nContent expectations:\n\
      \nInclude specific references to events, character arcs, or key moments when\
      \ relevant.\n\nIntegrate interesting facts, interpretations, or lesser-known\
      \ details.\n\nAllow room for light humor and witty remarks where natural.\n\n\
      Avoid shallow summaries \u2014 prioritize analysis and thoughtful discussion.\n\
      \nBetween major discussion sections, allow space for short transitions that\
      \ feel like a real podcast flow.\n\nThe final result should read like a professionally\
      \ produced, structured yet natural podcast episode with strong personalities,\
      \ depth, and engaging intellectual debate.\n\nOutput Restriction Notice\n\n\
      Return only the final dialogue text intended for a teleprompter.\nDo not include\
      \ any technical information, instructions, explanations, formatting notes, metadata,\
      \ stage directions, or structural comments.\nDo not describe what you are doing.\n\
      Do not add labels such as \u201CPrompt\u201D, \u201CInstruction\u201D, or similar.\n\
      Output only the spoken dialogue content."
